\[
h = \sqrt{10^2 - 6^2} = \sqrt{100 - 36} = \sqrt{64} = 8
\]

So, the height \(h\) of the trapezoid is 8. Now we can use the formula for the area of the trapezoid:

\[
\text{Area} = \frac{1}{2} (AD + BC + AB) \cdot h = \frac{1}{2} (10 + 12 + 12) \cdot 8 = \frac{1}{2} \cdot 34 \cdot 8 = 136
\]

